#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn53.45-54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 53 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 53 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:0.2"
msgid "5. Oghavagga "
msgstr "5. Floods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:0.3"
msgid "45–54. Oghādisutta "
msgstr "45–54 Floods, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.310, sc1
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro jhānā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "The four absorptions should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.8"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.9"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.10"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.11"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro jhānā bhāvetabbā”ti vitthāretabbaṃ. "
msgstr "These four absorptions should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.12"
msgid "(Yathā maggasaṃyuttaṃ tathā vitthāretabbaṃ.) "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in the Linked Discourses on the Path at SN 45.171–180.) "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:1.13"
msgid "Oghavaggo pañcamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:2.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:2.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca; "
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, "
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:2.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. "
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn53.45-54:2.5"
msgid "Jhānasaṃyuttaṃ navamaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Absorption are the ninth section."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
